FULL LAB EXERCISE — FROM ZERO TO RESULTS

PHASE 1 — Create Maven Project (Local System)
 Step 1 — Create project folder
D:
mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example.app -DartifactId=Ex9Devops -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false
Step 2 — Create the needed directories inside
src/main/java/com/example/app/
src/test/java/com/example/app/
 Step 3 — Create App.java file
Location:
D:\Ex9Devops\src\main\java\com\example\app\App.java
Content:
package com.example.app;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello World!");
    }
}

PHASE 2 — Create pom.xml (Runnable JAR)
Create this file inside:
D:\Ex9Devops\pom.xml
Paste this (final corrected pom.xml):
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example.app</groupId>
    <artifactId>demo-app</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <properties>
        <maven.compiler.source>8</maven.compiler.source>
        <maven.compiler.target>8</maven.compiler.target>
    </properties>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.13.2</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <!-- Makes JAR executable -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-jar-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.2.0</version>
                <configuration>
                    <archive>
                        <manifest>
                            <mainClass>com.example.app.App</mainClass>
                        </manifest>
                    </archive>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>

✅ PHASE 3 — Build the Project Locally
Open CMD:
cd D:\Ex9Devops
mvn clean package
A JAR will be created:
target/demo-app-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
✅ This verifies your code builds successfully.

✅ PHASE 4 — Push Code to GitHub
In CMD:
cd D:\Ex9Devops

git init
git config --global --add safe.directory D:/Ex9Devops

git add .
git commit -m "Initial project with runnable jar"

git branch -M main

git remote add origin https://github.com/<yourname>/demo-app.git

git push -u origin main
✅ Code is now on GitHub.

✅ PHASE 5 — Create Jenkins Pipeline Job
Step 1 — Open Jenkins

http://localhost:your -port number
Step 2 — Create a new job
✔ Click New Item
✔ Name: Maven-Pipeline-Demo
✔ Select: Pipeline
✔ Click OK

✅ PHASE 6 — Add Jenkins Pipeline Script
Scroll down to Pipeline → Pipeline Script
Paste this final working Jenkinsfile:
pipeline {
    agent any

    tools {
        maven "maven-3.9.11"
        jdk "jdk-17"
    }

    stages {

        stage('Checkout Code') {
            steps {
                git branch: 'main',
                    url: 'https://github.com/<yourname>/demo-app.git'
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                bat "mvn clean compile"
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                bat "mvn test"
            }
        }

        stage('Package') {
            steps {
                bat "mvn package"
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        always {
            archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'target/*.jar', fingerprint: true
        }
        success {
            echo "✅ Pipeline Success!"
        }
        failure {
            echo "❌ Pipeline Failed!"
        }
    }
}
✅ Replace <yourname> with your GitHub username.
Click Save.

✅ PHASE 7 — Run the Pipeline
Click:
✅ Build Now
You will see all stages:
✅ Checkout Code
✅ Build
✅ Test
✅ Package
✅ Artifact Saved
✅ Build Success!

✅ PHASE 8 — Download the Output JAR (Method 3)
On the left:
✅ Click Build # → Artifacts
✅ Download:
demo-app-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

✅ PHASE 9 — Run the JAR and See Output
Open CMD:
cd D:\Downloads
java -jar demo-app-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
You will see the output:
Hello World!

